This paper discusses a query processing system for data-intensive workloads in scientific databases, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper focuses on optimizing query processing in large datasets. The second most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper discusses executing queries concurrently and maximizing data sharing among queries. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new approach to scheduling queries based on data-driven batch processing. The fourth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper discusses techniques for improving query response time. The fifth likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a new system for query processing.
